T~L~35~-930~0~#0000FF~~9pt~~~~comment~Map for Nets:
(c) means interfacing with the computer and (m) means interfacing with memory
(o) means output and (i) means input
 
(c)(o)(i) Bus[x]: The base data bus that communicates with the rest of the computer.
(c)(i) MADIn: Indicates the target memory address is on the bus (also causes the ram to read and clear)(min width of 250ns)
(c)(i) RamIn: Tells the ram to write the data on the bus to the address.
(c)(i) RamOut: Tells the ram to output the data at the address to the bus (also causes the ram to rewrite old data).
 
(m)(o) MADX[x]: Indicates which x position in the memory grid is being accessed (target address).
(m)(o) MADY[x]: Indicates which y position in the memory grid is being accessed (target address).
 
(m)(o) ReadReq: Request new data to be read from the target address. (May take up to 1000ns after signal rise for MAD bus to be set)
(m)(i) ReadIn[x]: The data stored at the target address. 
(m)(i) ReadAvail: New data available on the ReadIn bus.
 
(m)(o) WriteReq: Request data to be written to the target address. (May take up to 500ns after signal rise for WriteOut bus to have data)
(m)(o) WriteOut[x]: The data to be written to the target address.
 
(c)(m)(i) MADDis: Disable the MADX and MADY buses (pulldown or short to ground if unused).
(c)(m)(i) WriteDis: Set the WriteOut bus to all zeros (pulldown or short to ground if unused).~1~start~gge9660~0~pinpart
